<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - INSTALL - RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
        <title>RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the small, flat reverse idler gear front washer on the pin in the lower right of the
                case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024d9">Figure 139</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024d9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024d9" filename="../figg13/G13024D9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 139. Install Reverse Idler Gear Front Washer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set reverse gear in position next to the washer, machined surface of the gear hub to the
                rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024e0">Figure 140</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024e0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024e0" filename="../figg13/G13024E0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 140. Set Reverse Gear in Position</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install needle bearing through the rear bore and into the hub of reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024e1">Figure 141</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024e1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024e1" filename="../figg13/G13024E1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 141. Install Needle Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the rear washer in the holder if previously removed, oil slot down, and bend lugs to
                secure the washer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the washer and holder into reverse gear case bore, oil slots toward the gear, holder
                flange to the rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024e2">Figure 142</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024e2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024e2" filename="../figg13/G13024E2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 142. Place Washer and Holder into Reverse Gear Case Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary countershaft front bearing into the reverse gear case bore to hold the
                reverse idler gear assembly in position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024e3">Figure 143</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024e3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024e3" filename="../figg13/G13024E3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 143. Install Auxiliary Countershaft Front Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The front portion of the auxiliary countershaft is used as a journal for the reverse idler gear.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
